  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Urban Community Participation in Engineering Design and Interventions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Construction of community based wastewater treatment units would alleviate the public and environmental health threat in reasonable timeframe. Community participation and buy into the design is key. Funding cycles are too short to address innovation in both community participation and engineering design. As most participatory tools are designed for rural settings, we would pilot tools for urban communities in engineering design, building upon experience involving urban communities in PHP. The results are approximately 9 WWT pilot units for 5 -6 households each (50 families total) validated by community and scientific data.</narrative>
  </description>
